Class UnitTest

java.lang.Object
UnitTest
public class UnitTest extends Object
UnitTesting is essential *after* you work through a method, and have it running. It helps you check for boundary conditions, and make sure your code is working. This class only contains the unit tests, and should only be called when wanting to run the tests for the program, over the actual application itself.
